# Works with VS Code REST Client and JetBrains HTTP Client.

@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:5678
@userId = paste-user-id-here

### Health: liveness
GET {{baseUrl}}/healthz

### Health: readiness, checks PostgreSQL connection
GET {{baseUrl}}/readyz

### Create user, run this before list/search examples
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ada Lovelace",
  "email": "ada-{{$timestamp}}@example.com"
}

### Get user by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{userId}}

### Update user by id
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{userId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ada Byron",
  "email": "ada.byron-{{$timestamp}}@example.com"
}

### Delete user by id
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{userId}}

### List users
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users

### Search users with cursor pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users?search=ada&limit=10

### Next users page, paste next_cursor from the previous response
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users?search=ada&limit=10&cursor=

### User stats
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/stats
